<subSubSection pageId="82" pageNumber="83" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="82.[151,1437,150,861]" pageId="82" pageNumber="83">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,438,464]" pageId="82" pageNumber="83">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Shinohara" authorityYear="1988" box="[322,581,438,464]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="82" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ussuriensis">
<emphasis box="[322,581,438,464]" italics="true" pageId="82" pageNumber="83">Pamphilius ussuriensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Shinohara" authorityYear="1988" box="[637,765,439,464]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="82" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zinovjevi">
<emphasis box="[637,765,439,464]" italics="true" pageId="82" pageNumber="83">P. zinovjevi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were described from the 
<typeStatus box="[1051,1160,438,464]" pageId="82" pageNumber="83">holotypes</typeStatus>
only. The 
<typeStatus box="[1280,1378,438,464]" pageId="82" pageNumber="83">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Shinohara" authorityYear="1988" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="82" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ussuriensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="82" pageNumber="83">P. ussuriensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a rather poorly preserved (discoloured) male specimen (
<figureCitation box="[933,1028,474,501]" captionStart="FIGURE 125" captionStartId="214.[151,250,1748,1772]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1722]" captionTargetId="figure-26@214.[151,1435,181,1724]" captionTargetPageId="214" captionText="FIGURE 125. Pamphilius ussuriensis, male, Russia (holotype) – (a) dorsally, (b) lateroventrally, (c) head &amp; thorax dorsally, (d) head antenna dorsolaterally, (e) face." pageId="82" pageNumber="83">Fig. 125</figureCitation>
) and that of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Shinohara" authorityYear="1988" box="[1169,1297,475,500]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="82" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zinovjevi">
<emphasis box="[1169,1297,475,500]" italics="true" pageId="82" pageNumber="83">P. zinovjevi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is an exceptionally small female specimen (
<figureCitation box="[512,646,510,536]" captionStart="FIGURE 126" captionStartId="215.[151,250,1869,1893]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1845]" captionTargetId="figure-19@215.[151,1435,181,1845]" captionTargetPageId="215" captionText="FIGURE 126. Pamphilius ussuriensis (specimen 86348 and holotype of P. zinovjevi), female, Russia – (a) head &amp; thorax dorsally (86348), (b) head &amp; thorax ventrolaterally (86348), (c) face (86348), (d) dorsally, (e) lateroventrally, (f) face." pageId="82" pageNumber="83">Fig. 126d–f</figureCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Shinohara, A." box="[656,848,510,536]" pageId="82" pageNumber="83" pagination="307 - 320" refId="ref76348" refString="Shinohara, A. (1988 a) The group of Pamphilius sylvaticus (Hymenoptera, Pamphiliidae): Five new species and additional records from the Far East. Kontyu, Tokyo, 56, 307 - 320." type="journal article" year="1988">Shinohara 1988a</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Shinohara, A." box="[867,1061,510,536]" pageId="82" pageNumber="83" pagination="99 - 116" refId="ref76721" refString="Shinohara, A. (2001) The group of Pamphilius sylvaticus (Hymenoptera, Pamphiliidae): Two new species, new collection records, and a key to Palearctic species. Japanese Journal of Systematic Entomology, 7, 99 - 116." type="journal article" year="2001">Shinohara (2001)</bibRefCitation>
examined five additional females of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Shinohara" authorityYear="1988" box="[182,311,547,572]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="82" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zinovjevi">
<emphasis box="[182,311,547,572]" italics="true" pageId="82" pageNumber="83">P. zinovjevi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Primorskij Kraj and 
<collectingCountry box="[613,754,546,573]" name="South Korea" pageId="82" pageNumber="83">South Korea</collectingCountry>
and discussed the variation among them. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Shinohara" authorityYear="1988" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="82" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ussuriensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="82" pageNumber="83">Pamphilius ussuriensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was only known from the 
<typeStatus box="[511,609,582,608]" pageId="82" pageNumber="83">holotype</typeStatus>
male until now. The COI sequences of the newly obtained specimens of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Shinohara" authorityYear="1988" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="82" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ussuriensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="82" pageNumber="83">P. ussuriensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(a male, DEI-GISHym 21853, and a female, DEI-GISHym 86348, initially determined as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Shinohara" authorityYear="1988" box="[1299,1427,619,644]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="82" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zinovjevi">
<emphasis box="[1299,1427,619,644]" italics="true" pageId="82" pageNumber="83">P. zinovjevi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) were retrieved as monophyletic with 100% UFBoot support (
<figureCitation box="[859,960,654,680]" captionStart="FIGURE 146" captionStartId="233.[151,250,1448,1472]" captionTargetBox="[157,1428,188,1418]" captionTargetId="figure-19@233.[151,1436,181,1424]" captionTargetPageId="233" captionText="FIGURE 146. Condensed ML tree based on CO1 gene sequences, with details of Pamphilius sylvaticus group, part 2." pageId="82" pageNumber="83">Fig. 146</figureCitation>
). Though the 
<specimenCount box="[1123,1291,654,681]" pageId="82" pageNumber="83" type="generic">two specimens</specimenCount>
diverged by 1.8% in COI, it now seems reasonable to regard them as different sexes of the same species and here we propose to treat 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Shinohara" authorityYear="1988" box="[208,335,727,752]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="82" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zinovjevi">
<emphasis box="[208,335,727,752]" italics="true" pageId="82" pageNumber="83">P. zinovjevi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a synonym of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Shinohara" authorityYear="1988" box="[532,683,727,752]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="82" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ussuriensis">
<emphasis box="[532,683,727,752]" italics="true" pageId="82" pageNumber="83">P. ussuriensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="82.[151,1437,150,861]" pageId="82" pageNumber="83">
This species belongs to the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Linne" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[503,640,762,788]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="82" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sylvaticus">
<emphasis box="[503,640,762,788]" italics="true" pageId="82" pageNumber="83">P. sylvaticus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group (
<bibRefCitation author="Shinohara, A." box="[725,921,762,788]" pageId="82" pageNumber="83" pagination="359 - 438" refId="ref76809" refString="Shinohara, A. (2002 b) Systematics of the leaf-rolling or webspinning sawfly subfamily Pamphiliinae: a preliminary overview. In: Viitasaari, M. (Ed.), Sawflies (Hymenoptera, Symphyta) I. Tremex Press, Helsinki, pp. 359 - 438." type="book chapter" year="2002">Shinohara 2002b</bibRefCitation>
). Diverging by a minimum of 4.8% in the COI sequences, the nearest neighbour was 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Shinohara &amp; Kramp &amp; Taeger" authorityYear="2022" box="[572,725,798,824]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="82" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="graciloides">
<emphasis box="[572,725,798,824]" italics="true" pageId="82" pageNumber="83">P. graciloides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, according to our molecular analysis. In the COI tree (
<figureCitation box="[1327,1423,798,824]" captionStart="FIGURE 146" captionStartId="233.[151,250,1448,1472]" captionTargetBox="[157,1428,188,1418]" captionTargetId="figure-19@233.[151,1436,181,1424]" captionTargetPageId="233" captionText="FIGURE 146. Condensed ML tree based on CO1 gene sequences, with details of Pamphilius sylvaticus group, part 2." pageId="82" pageNumber="83">Fig. 146</figureCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Shinohara" authorityYear="1988" box="[151,303,835,860]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="82" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ussuriensis">
<emphasis box="[151,303,835,860]" italics="true" pageId="82" pageNumber="83">P. ussuriensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Eversmann, 1847)" baseAuthorityName="Eversmann" baseAuthorityYear="1847" box="[358,708,834,860]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="82" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jucundus">
<emphasis box="[358,486,834,860]" italics="true" pageId="82" pageNumber="83">P. jucundus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Eversmann, E." box="[501,699,834,860]" pageId="82" pageNumber="83" pagination="3 - 68" refId="ref73264" refString="Eversmann, E. (1847) Fauna hymenopterologica volgo-uralensis exhibens Hymenopterorum species quas in provinciis Volgam fluvium inter et montes Uralenses sitis observavit et nunc descripsit. Bulletin de la Societe Imperiale des Naturalistes de Moscou, 20, 3 - 68." type="journal article" year="1847">Eversmann, 1847</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
formed a monophyletic group with 99% UFBoot support.
</paragraph>
